kfritz (0.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fixed TR-064 auth: a preemptive Basic Authorization header stopped Qt
    from negotiating Digest auth, which FRITZ!Box requires — every SOAP
    call was failing with 401.
  * Fixed the phonebook list in Settings never refreshing after a fetch
    (missing phonebookDownloaded signal emission).
  * Added a visible explanation of the Contacts/Blocklist write-target
    concept in Settings.
  * Brought all 5 translations (de/fr/es/nl/ru) up to date with the
    Contacts/Blocklist feature.

 -- Agundur <info@agundur.de>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 07:00:00 +0200

kfritz (0.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fixed OBS build failure (RPM only, unrelated to the .deb): %files was
    missing %dir declarations for the qml/de and qml/de/agundur parent
    directories, flagged as unowned by the openSUSE lint step.

 -- Agundur <info@agundur.de>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 15:00:00 +0200

kfritz (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Sound on incoming call (closes #7).
  * Phonebook/blocklist quick-actions: caller ID lookup and blocking now
    check multiple phonebooks per role, with one designated write target
    each so a WebDAV-synced blocklist can't get overwritten.
  * Missed calls from while the widget wasn't running are now caught up
    on startup via the FritzBox's own call list.
  * CMakeLists.txt no longer requires a giant unused KDE Workspace KCM
    dependency set; fixed a bug shipping raw plugin sources as data files.
  * Fixed "KKFritz" typo in metadata.json.

 -- Agundur <info@agundur.de>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 14:00:00 +0200

